PAT McGRATH LABS LAUNCHES SKIN FETISH SUBLIME PERFECTION SETTING SPRAY
headings: pat mcgrath labs launches skin fetish sublime perfection setting spray& new under-eye blurring powder shades “peach” and “amber”
pat mcgrath’s latest innovation delivers a weightless, soft-focus veil for 16+ hour wear.

"i’ve always believed a setting spray should do more than just hold — it should transform. this is my latest backstage breakthrough: weightless, blurring, and built to keep makeup major from first application to final look."

pat mcgrath labs unveils the new skin fetish: sublime perfection longwear blurring setting spray — a skincare-powered mist that hydrates, blurs, and boosts radiance in one whisper-thin veil. from the runway to real life, use it as the final step in your makeup routine, misting the face evenly and reapplying as a refreshing boost throughout the day. makeup will maintain its vibrancy for 16+ hours, as the longwear blurring setting spray is engineered to withstand heat, humidity, and smudging, while delivering a multidimensional, soft-focus finish. not to mention, it’s alcohol-free and fragrance-free, as well as free of clay and silica so no powdery residue or whitecast. pat shared with forbes “i never release anything i haven’t tested on real faces in real time—red carpets, runways, flashbulbs, all-night affairs. the spray and powder worked in every condition. seamless wear, luminous blur, no touchups needed. they proved they belong on every stage and in every kit.”

pair the new skin fetish: sublime perfection longwear blurring setting spray with pat’s iconic under-eye blurring powder — now available in seven total versatile shades, including new peach and amber shades, specifically created with medium to deeper skin tones in mind. the powder smooths texture, blurs pores, and provides a perfecting, soft-focus effect under the eyes as well as all over the face.

the new skin fetish: sublime perfection longwear blurring setting spray and new peach and amber shades of the skin fetish: sublime perfection blurring under-eye powder are available now at patmcgrath.com, and will be available at sephora.com starting september 1st, available in-store at sephora starting september 5th, and available at all other retailers - including nordstrom, bergdorf goodman, ulta beauty, revolve and  bluemercury- starting september 25th.
